    <h1>WHO AM I?</h1>
    <p>Hey there! I'm <b>Shibagni Bhattacharjee</b>, currently diving into the exciting world of B.Tech CSE at the <b>University of Engineering and Management</b>. I had a solid foundation thanks to my CBSE schooling – it really set the stage for my journey in <b>computer science and engineering</b>.
      Jaipur was a blast for me as I took on various courses to expand my horizons. Those experiences were gold! They shaped my understanding and added a whole toolbox of skills to my repertoire. Learning there wasn't just about textbooks; it was hands-on and dynamic, which totally fired up my passion.
      I'm always on the lookout for new knowledge. Whether it's diving into coursework, getting involved in research, or applying what I've learned, I'm all in. Staying updated with the latest tech trends keeps me buzzing, and I love exploring how those advancements apply in the real world.
      But it's not just about solo learning for me. I thrive when collaborating with others. Team settings? Count me in! I'm all about sharing ideas, pooling our strengths, and solving challenges together. Connecting with peers, learning from their perspectives – it's where the real magic happens.
      My journey at the University of Engineering and Management is just one part of my story. Combined with my diverse educational background and my hunger to soak up all things tech, I'm on this journey to rock the world of computer science and engineering!
      Keep learning, keep growing, and let's code some incredible stuff together! </p>
