    <p>created a calculator in Python involves building a program that performs basic arithmetic operations like addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division. It typically takes user input for numbers and the desired operation, then computes and displays the result. This project often utilizes functions, conditional statements, and loops to handle user interactions and perform calculations accurately. The interface could be text-based in the terminal or a simple graphical user interface (GUI) using libraries like Tkinter.</p>
